text: Nordschwarzwaldturm (Tower of Northern Black Forest) is the name of a free standing steel framework tower near Schoemberg-Langenbrand in the Black Forest. The Nordschwarzwaldturm was built in 1974 and is used for directional radio services, FM- and TV-transmissions.
